{
  "stem": "22972.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Still and all, for a typical family of four people, it took $20,000, which was a fortune in the early '30s, during the Depression.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "You had to post somehow or other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And the $5,000 was very simply that it took five years to become an American citizen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And in those days, they figured that it took approximately $1,000 a year to exist, so that the Jews that came in under this quota would never become a burden on the government.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "That we would not ask for welfare, like people do today.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we had a rich uncle who kept saying, month after month after month, I have great connections in Washington and I have been told that Hitler will not last more than another two months.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This went on for five years until my mother went to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother had a connection in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She supposedly had a gynecologist there that she went to see.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What she did was she paid this gentleman in Carlsbad, which is now Karlovy Vary in Czechoslovakia, to send letters to America, and receive letters.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he would make a phone call every time my uncle would write.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And finally, he gave us my-- the affidavit is dated January, 1938.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father, because he was such a big shot in World War I and, as I said, was protected until the day we left Germany, was taken ahead.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It-- in-- in January of 1938, it took at least two or three years to stand in line to get a quarter number.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father got the quarter within 24 hours, got the number, and we made preparations.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We packed up and we left Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
